Areva, EDF, Energies Nouvelles, Total: French Equity Preview

-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 
2011-04-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/areva-edf-energies-nouvelles-total-french-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Paris. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names and prices are from the last close.  The benchmark CAC Index rose 0.8 percent to 4,061.91. The
broader SBF 120 increased 0.7 percent to 3,045.21.  Areva SA (CEI)  : The nuclear-reactor maker has bought a
34 percent stake in atomic-power joint venture Areva NP from
Siemens AG for 1.62 billion euros ($2.34 billion), Die Welt
reported, citing an unidentified Siemens spokesperson. Areva
shares rose 0.2 percent to 31.155 euros.  EDF Energies Nouvelles SA (EEN)  : The renewable-energy
company’s chairman, Paris Mouratoglou, has agreed to sell his 25
percent stake to Electricite de France SA, which offered by buy
out minority shareholders for about a 10 percent premium over
the last traded price. The shares will resume trading following
an April 8 suspension for the announcement. They rose 0.3
percent to 36.64 euros previously.  Electricite de France SA (EDF FP): The nuclear utility’s
shares will resume trading after a suspension April 8 ahead of
an offer to buy the 50 percent it doesn’t already own of
renewable energy unit EDF Energies Nouvelles for as much as 1.5
billion euros. The stock slipped 0.6 percent to 27.38 euros
previously.  Total SA (FP)  : The  oil company  is in exclusive talks
with private equity firm Klesch & Co. Ltd. for the sale in its
Lindsey refinery in the U.K. for as much as 2 billion pounds
($3.3 billion), the Sunday Telegraph reported, without saying
where it got the information. The shares rose 0.7 percent to
43.15 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
